<br>
<span>B. Rewrite the following sentences with the adverbs in the appropriate place.<br></span>
<br>
 <span>i. I watch television. (often)<br></span>
<br>
Ans: I often watch television.<br>
<br>
<span>ii. Have you been to Janakput? (ever)<br></span>
<br>
Ans: Have you ever been to Janakpur.<br>
<br>
<span>iii. They play football on Saturday. (sometimes)<br></span>
<br>
Ans: They sometimes play football on Saturday.<br>
<br>
<span>iv. The weather is bad in November. (always)<br></span>
<br>
Ans: The weather is always bad in November. <br>
<br>
<span>v. We have fish for dinner. (seldom)<br></span>
<br>
Ans: We seldom have fish for dinner.<br>
<br>
<span>vi. Pritam doesn&rsquo;t get up before seven. (usually)<br></span>
<br>
Ans: Pritam usually gets up after seven.<br>
<br>
<span>vii. I was very tired and I was hungry. (also)<br></span>
<br>
Ans: I was very tired and I was also hungry.<br>
<br>
<span>viii. Did you enjoy the flight? (both)<br></span>
<br>
Ans: Did you both enjjoy the flight?<br>
